begin_memory_text: We talked about coronavirus and being in quarantine. They mentioned that they've been cooking more and we talked about baking. I can't exactly remember what we talked about in the very beginning because much of the conversation revolved around the same topic of shared struggles being in quarantine so I can't remember the order they came in. I think we mentioned that we were both unemployed at the start.
middle_memory_text: We talked about college and out degrees. They had a dual major in physics and gender studies. We talked about similar websites to prolific like focus groups. We talked about anime and tv shows, they're watching korra. We talked about how our friends were also struggling to find jobs.
end_memory_text: We talked more about quarantine and hoping that things get better for both of us. I asked if it was their first time doing these conversations and they said yes. Again I can't really remember exact start, middle, and end of the conversation because I think we stuck to one topic for most of the conversation because we talked about covid a lot.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well. I don't have much planned and that worries me a bit because I don't want to end up bored with nothing to do since it would make me bored. I'm hoping to hear good news back from my job search. I'd say overall I feel hopeful.
critical_positive: I think what worked well with the conversation is that we found a shared struggle that we were both facing that we could talk about, that being our difficulty finding a job out of college in the current situation. I also think the conversation went well because again we were both trying to have a conversation and dedicated the time for it. I think were it not for that our conversation would have ended earlier.
critical_negative: I think what didn't work as well was I got the impression that neither of us were super outgoing people. So there were pauses in the conversation because neither of us had something to talk about but we would both try to keep the conversation going regardless. I also felt a little bad if we said something at the same time, they seemed apologetic for it though they didn't need to be.

begin_memory_text: Names. COVID. Siblings. My partner plays music; I did martial arts.
middle_memory_text: Job searching. Swapping some references. Also, talking about our schooling.
end_memory_text: Job stuff. Sharing information. Waiting for the 25 minutes to end. Wishing each other luck. Partner's sister's schooling.
rest_of_day_open: My week will probably be fine--about normal for me. It'll have a little stress, since I need to plan out the meals. I'll also be a bit worried about money. My fatigue will probably still be a problem. But, overall, if I manage my expectations, then my emotions should be ok. So, maybe "decent"?
critical_positive:
I felt like my conversation partner was trying to keep the conversation going. They seemed to have a few questions prepared--maybe they planned them beforehand? or simply thought of them during the conversation.

My partner also seemed pleasant. A little socially awkward, but so am I. I am familiar with socially awkward people, too, so it actually felt a bit reassuring.
critical_negative:
There were sometimes where we had breaks in the conversation without much development. There were a few times where I dropped the momentum or where I started to get caught up in emotions, too.

Also, I feel like I sometimes took up more of the time. I tend to ask people a lot of questions, and I feel like I probably asked more questions of them then they did of me. I hope that I didn't leave a poor impression.
